    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** (70.02) leading the charge, as he faces a favorable matchup against the right-handed Schlittler. **Henderson**\u2019s elite lead-off placement and a strong platoon advantage provide the highest ceiling on the roster. He is joined in the top tier by **Josh Lowe** (69.30) and **Heliot Ramos** (69.27), both of whom are poised for production due to high-leverage lineup slots and beneficial environmental factors. Specifically, the \"wind out\" condition and a plus matchup against Randy V\u00e1squez provide **Ramos** a significant boost, while **Lowe** benefits from a soft 4.38 xERA from Davis Martin. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (65.92) also remains a core anchor today; despite a neutral platoon, his ability to punish the 4.59 xERA of Martinez ensures he remains an essential start despite the park factor penalty.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the lineup optimizer involved **Dominic Smith** (36.41), who hovered on the edge of consideration but ultimately fell short of the starting rotation. While his platoon advantage against Logan Gilbert provided a marginal lift, the combination of a tough opposing arm and a lower-tier batting order position cemented his place on the bench. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Drake Baldwin**, **Sam Antonacci**, **Miguel Vargas**, and **Jackson Merrill**. Should their assumed batting order positions shift downward once official lineups are released, their efficiency scores\u2014particularly for **Baldwin** and **Merrill**, who face the formidable Logan Gilbert and Trevor McDonald respectively\u2014could drop below our preferred floor. \n\nRisk management remains paramount as we navigate these matchups, particularly with the elite arm of Logan Gilbert potentially stifling **Baldwin** and the lower half of the order. While **Kyle Tucker** (57.97) and **Andy Pages** (50.24) are solid, their output against the left-handed Okert requires careful monitoring, as the platoon disadvantage narrows their upside compared to the rest of the outfield corps. As always, our injury-depleted depth\u2014including **Jordan Westburg** and **Luis Robert Jr.**\u2014means we have limited flexibility if these games are rained out or if late lineup changes force us to rely on secondary options. We continue to monitor the status of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, **Coby Mayo**, and **Brady House** for potential rotation updates later this week.",
